.TH "__ssam_device_driver_register" 9 "__ssam_device_driver_register" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__ssam_device_driver_register \- Register a SSAM client device driver.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" __ssam_device_driver_register
.BI "(struct ssam_device_driver *sdrv "  ","
.BI "struct module *owner "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sdrv" 12
The driver to register.
.IP "owner" 12
The module owning the provided driver.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Please refer to the \fBssam_device_driver_register\fP macro for the normal way
to register a driver from inside its owning module.
